 :macdink: /mak'dink/ [from the Apple Macintosh, which is said to encourage
such behavior] vt. To make many incremental and unnecessary cosmetic changes
to a program or file. Often the subject of the macdinking would be better off
without them. "When I left at 11 P.M. last night, he was still macdinking the
slides for his presentation." see also {fritterware}.